---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="GRC Automation Tool | Aryan">
  <section class="section-padding">
    <div class="mx-auto w-full max-w-container px-6">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.35em] text-white/50">Project</p>
        <h1 class="mt-4 font-heading text-4xl">Airflow-Based GRC Automation Pipeline</h1>
        <p class="mt-3 text-white/60">NIST CM-8 Asset Intelligence · Segregation of Duties · DPDPA Privacy Controls</p>
        <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
          <a
            href="https://github.com/Aryanb1102/GRC-Automation-Tool-"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noreferrer"
            class="rounded-xl border border-white/20 px-6 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-white/80 transition hover:text-white"
          >
            GitHub repo
          </a>
        </div>
        <div class="article-content mt-10">
          <h2>Problem Context</h2>
          <p>
            Modern organizations operate complex digital environments where security, compliance, and privacy checks
            must be performed continuously. Teams must verify that infrastructure assets are properly inventoried, user
            privileges do not create fraud risks, and personal data is handled according to regulatory requirements.
          </p>
          <p>
            These processes are often handled through manual audits or fragmented scripts, leading to delayed detection
            of violations and weak audit trails. Enterprise GRC tools exist, but they are frequently expensive and
            difficult to customize.
          </p>
          <p>
            This project explores how workflow orchestration and policy-as-code can automate core compliance controls
            while maintaining transparency and auditability.
          </p>

          <h2>System Objective</h2>
          <p>
            The goal was to build an automated GRC control engine that continuously executes security and compliance
            checks across three domains:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Asset Intelligence (NIST CM-8) – maintain accurate infrastructure inventories</li>
            <li>Identity Governance – detect Segregation of Duties (SoD) violations</li>
            <li>Data Privacy Compliance – identify and sanitize personal data in development environments</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            The system emphasizes continuous monitoring, structured evidence generation, and clear traceability between
            control runs and detected violations.
          </p>

          <h2>Architecture &amp; Design</h2>
          <p>
            The pipeline runs on Apache Airflow inside a Docker environment with a PostgreSQL backend.
          </p>
          <p>Airflow DAGs execute compliance controls and produce structured outputs:</p>
          <p>Control Run → Detection Logic → Findings → Evidence Artifacts → Postgres Storage</p>
          <p>
            A control registry (controls.yaml) defines each compliance rule, allowing new controls to be added without
            modifying core workflow code.
          </p>
          <p>PostgreSQL tables store the operational audit trail:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>controls – registered governance checks</li>
            <li>runs – execution history</li>
            <li>findings – detected violations</li>
            <li>evidence – generated artifacts</li>
          </ul>
          <p>Each run also generates JSON summaries and CSV evidence files.</p>

          <h2>Key Modules</h2>
          <p>Asset Intelligence</p>
          <p>
            Simulates asset inventory ingestion and archival. The pipeline records host metadata and prepares the
            foundation for future reconciliation against infrastructure scans.
          </p>
          <p>Segregation of Duties Detection</p>
          <p>
            Evaluates user roles against policy rules to detect toxic privilege combinations such as “Create Vendor +
            Approve Payment.” Violations are logged with severity and supporting evidence.
          </p>
          <p>Privacy Violation Response</p>
          <p>
            Scans development datasets for sensitive identifiers (e.g., SSN patterns). Detected values are hashed and
            sanitized, producing anonymized datasets and violation reports.
          </p>

          <h2>Operational Insights</h2>
          <p>
            The system demonstrates how policy-driven automation can replace periodic audits with continuous compliance
            monitoring. Evidence generation, persistent findings, and configuration-based controls create a transparent
            audit trail suitable for security operations and regulatory review.
          </p>

          <h2>Next Steps</h2>
          <p>
            Future improvements include asset reconciliation, retention policy enforcement, alert integrations, and a
            web dashboard for control monitoring and findings management.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
